This package runs uses a Naive Bayes classifier to categorize files as spam or not spam
according to the presence or absence of various features.  A file of classified data (binary feature values and classification)
are supplied to main, and used to build the classifier.  A file of unclassified data (binary feature values) is also
supplied to main... and is classified by the built classifier. 

There is a single run option.
Run in eclipse, or from command line with: 
java -jar NaiveBayes spamLabelled.dat spamUnlabelled.dat


 

